name: Feral
description:
24" x 48" on wood
Acrylic, Pencil, Pastels

The Story:
Faces from the past. A priest disguised as a magician. a prince that is really a toad, and a wolf that lures them in by pretending he's a bunny with closed eyes. empty handed magician. Toad king, camel disappears, leaves water. False magician feeding drugs. not real magic. Rabbit blocks out lies but has big ears. this is difficult. he transforms into a wolf by just envisioning his power. pyramids protect. hop, hop, hope. magician is empty handed. toad king wants spells. reverse money symbol x3. he who controls time and space. gold coins. all they want is money. fulfill destiny. eggs hatch and explode. gold rains from the sky. toad king eat's the unicorn horn. eggs crack open and turn the sky dark. Blackness seeps in. dark camel fights the king. prince was a frog after all. magician and toad team up to kill the were-rabbit. mutating. elephant insect inside. you can't just expect a rabbit every time. shpynx. stegosaurus. wyrm. follow me down the rabid whole. sleeping rabbit merges with dreams and becomes the enlightened serpent. en-light-end. rabbit takes off mask. opens head. orbs. planet magic. gaea. birth to a comet to destroy the enemy. turn tail & run. en-light. ten. alien power. comet becomes full moon. transfix. transformed. catching up in the end. bite off more than you can chew. cerberus. 3x crosses. a reminder

© Davey Cadaver 2012

Video here: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UMKAj9RAXqE&feature=relmfu

name: Fox and the Hound (Friends Forever)
description:
24" x 48"
Acrylic, Pastel, Pencil, on Wood

Big Mama: Tod, that Copper is going to come back a hunting dog, a real killer.
Young Tod: Oh no, not my friend Copper. He won't ever change.
Big Mama: I hope you're right.
Young Tod: And we'll keep on being friends forever. Right, Big Mama?
Big Mama: Darling, forever is a long, long time, and time has a way of changing things.

description:
13" x 19"

Printed on Velvet Fine Art Paper with
Museum Quality Archival Inks.
Rated at over 90 Years.

This is an authentic print, signed and numbered by the artist.
Print Run of 100.

The Story:
Jumping on a wild bull. All I have is me. Magic, feathers, a leap of faith. All I have is me. Reaching up. Thank you for the venom.
No longer your pincushion, No more needles in my back. Shadows and voodoo dolls, my past speaks volumes for us all.
